Music style
The general musical style of ItaloBrothers (except "My Life Is a Party" and "This Is Nightlife") is comparable with dance bands or artists, mostly from Italy, like Bloom 06, Prezioso, Floorfilla, Gigi D'Agostino, Gabry Ponte, Basshunter or some releases of DJ Manian and has influences of Italo dance, Hands Up and Jumpstyle. They were also compared to Scooter.

In contrast to this, the music style of their singles "Cryin' In The Rain", "My Life Is a Party" and "This Is Nightlife" is mostly influenced by commercial European dance music like House and Electro. This style can be compared to artists like R.I.O., 2010s releases of Manian and Cascada, and Mike Candys.
